The proposed method in this study was implemented on a sound card (Fig. 8
). In Fig. 8, the structure of intelligence diagnosing avian diseases was programmed by using Code Composer Studio v.5 and C programming language. As shown in Fig. 9
, the chicken’s sound is processed using DWT and FFT. In the next step, 5 features, which were selected in feature selection part, will be extracted from the sound signal in frequency and time-frequency domains. Sequentially, the classes of the sound were determined by using SVM and finally, the outputs of SVM in frequency and time-frequency were combined by using D-S evidence theory.
